First Translation From Gibberish [i.e. Not spell/grammar checked] <br>
<br>
1. During the height of the Yellow Kingdom the psychotic minds began performing pilgrimages to neighboring towns. Traveling in pairs of 2-5 missionaries. These groups would walk crawl and flop about the streets spreading insanity with pamphlet and gifs [leaves and rocks they'd picked up on the way] <br>
<br>
2. The people of these towns found them a nuisance and began to fear the Yellow ones; they viewed them as a threat on civilized society. To combat the threat they began killing the yellow ones on sight. <br>
<br>
3. Word quickly spread to The Mad Man Of Yellow who became disturbed. It's hard to disturb a man already over the edge, but his disturbance was great so he met with his top advisors one by one. <br>
<br>
4. He met with The Great Sheep King in their great fields; he traveled to the mountains and spoke with The Goat. He walked the streets until he found The Lead Piper of Yellow and consulted him also. He went shrine to shrine until he found The Fanatic &quot;Path Follower&quot; who's conversation was pointless and accomplished nothing, as Path Follower simply tried to convince The Mad Man Of Yellow that their was no problem because nothing existed. <br>
<br>
5. This did not dampen The Mad Man Of Yellows spirits who then traveled to the ocean and spoke with The Yellow Prophet who believed he was a dolphin. In a very.. &quot;special&quot; way. [www.dolphinsex.com] The Yellow prophet offered advice as best he could. <br>
<br>
6. The Mad Man Of Yellow then traveled even farther down the beaches of the ocean to visit The Squid a man who believed he was a squid. This man confused him further by quoting from old Fireball and Skyline issues.. <br>
<br>
7. Thoroughly confused and unable to think straight, which definitely wasn't anything new. He began wandering until he found himself with his dear friend The Telepathic banana. He consulted his yellow fruit friend who informed him on what he was to do. <br>
<br>
8. On the dawn of the next day The Mad Man Of Yellow announced that he was forming the Yellow Crescent. Which was going to be the militia of the people to eradicate all those who followed the Path of red. <br>
<br>
9. Path of red stood for all those who shed blood in the name of sanity and all things civilized. They where the enemy of The Path Of Yellow because they would not accept the archetypes. All they knew was one archetype and that was the symbol of industry and conforming to secular beliefs. While The Yellow ones respected there right to these beliefs, they would no respect the sacrifice of their people. <br>
<br>
10. So The Yellow Crescent was formed and sent from the Yellow Kingdom to make war with The Path Of Red and all those who belonged to it. Wave after wave of wars ended in stalemates and defeats. <br>
<br>
11. Rumors began spreading amongst the Path of Yellow that they would lose the war. The propaganda grew and spread through out the land. The Yellow Crescent itself began to lose all hope. <br>
<br>
12. Then amongst the people a female spoke out by the name of Joan from the small town of arp. She came before the Mad Man Of Yellow promising victory if he let her lead the Yellow Crescent. She spoke saying &quot;The Telepathic banana has given me a sign that I will lead our people to victory over The Path of Red&quot;. So it was done, Joan Of Arp became the leader of the Yellow Crescent <br>
<br>
