The First War Of Mammals <br>
<br>
First Translation[ie. No spelling or grammar checks yet] <br>
<br>
Book of Preparation Part One <br>
<br>
1. The year is unknown since crazy men seem to either obsesses over time or forget it all together. Those who where so enthralled by the ticking, time tracking devices where pre occupied to inform the other members of the path of yellow. <br>
<br>
2. It was a turbulent time when the many factions in the path of yellow where presence. These factions took the form of animals as their symbols and physical manifestation. While shape shifting seems impossible now.. it may have been possible then.. or at least a bad trip. <br>
<br>
3. Two of the more well known factions are The House Of Sheep and The House of Goats. These two seemingly peaceful animals coexisted for years without distaste for the other house. While the other factions fought wars the two simply ate and crawled on all fours leaping like the crazy people. <br>
<br>
Book of Preparation Part Two <br>
<br>
1. Then The Mad Man Of Yellow published one of his earlier writings &quot;The Great Book of Banana&quot;. While the sheep and those who followed it where all very happy seeing as their leader was represented in this book as The Great Sheep King. The leader of the goats and his followers where not pleased. They felt betrayed by the actions of The Mad Man Of Yellow. So the leader of The House of Goats who was known as &quot;The Goat&quot; began a plot. <br>
<br>
2. This plot was not necessary simply because The Mad Man Of Yellow was insane and had not meant to not include the goat in the storyline however even the sheep believed it was to spite the goat so supported The Mad Man Of Yellow. <br>
<br>
3. The House of Goats could not attack the Mad Man Of Yellow directly as that would be a direct assault on The Path Of Yellow making them an outcast to all other factions of this time. They instead decided to Wage war on the House of sheep. <br>
<br>
--- <br>
<br>
Two Horns Rising <br>
<br>
Book Of War Plans <br>
<br>
1. The Goat climbed to the tip of the mountain, this mountain was home of all The House Of Goats. The Goat stood on the mountain peak and meditated to articulate the proper plan for revenge. <br>
<br>
2. It came to him on the fifth day of meditation. They would storm The House of Sheep on the third day of the seventh week and burn it to the ground and plant banana tree's in the corpses of all the fallen sheep. <br>
<br>
3. The Goat informed all those loyal to the path of yellow and preservation of the Goat species. However one wandering Piper overheard his plot while playing his pipe for money. <br>
<br>
4. He warned The Mad Man Of Yellow who then informed all those loyal to the path of yellow and preservation of insanity. From these people word eventually leaked to the Great Sheep King of the path of yellow. <br>
<br>
5. Nobody said a word and acted like all things where insane and nothing normal would occur. However spies in The House of Sheep informed him of new fortifications and plans for war. He knew then that they knew but that the only way they could know, is if The Mad Man knew and told them. <br>
<br>
Book Of Medication <br>
<br>
1. Twice he had been betrayed by The Mad Man of Yellow.. or so he thought he knew he had but he hadn't known.. or something. <br>
<br>
2. None the less he began a new wave of plots. This time using the foribben medication that causes sanity and clearness of mind. Upon receiving the knowledge that came as thd dizziness faded.. he then truely knew all things sane. <br>
<br>
3. It disturbed him.. it disturbed him greatly and he went mad.. again. During his round of born again insanity he killed a goat that had been used for milking. His people at first ashamed but when they looked into his eyes knew he had taken of the medication of sanity and forgave him. <br>
<br>
4. He took the two small horns from the fallen goat and glued him to his head. He then explained the new plan for the eradication of The House of Sheep. <br>
<br>
5. The House of Goats had then decided a plan that would cause the entire House Of Sheep to suffer as The Goat had and take of the medication of sanity and while in a state of confusion to lay their horned wrath down upon them <br>
<br>
--- <br>
<br>
Walking On Two Feet <br>
<br>
Beeeaah Beeeaah [Goat Language] <br>
Subtitle: Take that monkey [evil] lovers! <br>
<br>
<br>
1. The Sheep where very careful not to mention that they knew the plan. The Goat twice as careful having failed once to keep it secret. They had a spirit of determination about them. <br>
<br>
2. The Sheep slept it was the seventh day of the month and they had five guards watching over the House Of Sheep compound which was a field outside of the great temple. <br>
<br>
3. This night a band of six members of the house of Goat descended on the field, each had a pair of goat horns glued to their heads. The sheep on all fours guarded ready to call the alarm at the first sign of twin horns. <br>
<br>
4. The six came into view and head butted the four sheep by surprise knocking them unconscious. They then spread the powder medication over the field quickly and ran quickly up the fields hopping at random like the infamous mountain goats. <br>
<br>
5. They then hid on the mountain ledge and waited for Dawn. In the morning they would descend on the confused sheep. <br>
<br>
Baaah Baaaah <br>
<br>
Subtitle: What the @#%$ <br>
<br>
1. As the house of sheep woke up they went to their regular feeding ground that was now covered with white powder and four sleeping guards. Slightly confused they thought it a sign from heaven. <br>
<br>
2. They began partaking of the powder covered grass eating it and hopping about as sheep do sometimes. They then when full of the psychotropic substance began seeing things clearly. <br>
<br>
3. Their visions corrected.. they now felt very silly as the visions and tranquil feeling of true insanity dripped from their psychotic minds. They began standing up right and walking on two feet still in a slightly confused state. <br>
<br>
4. Then they heard in the background bleeaaah bleeeaah sounds as if a man was pretending he was a Goat. Just then a group of twenty three goat warriors descended upon them head butting them. <br>
<br>
5. The sheep who hadn't partaken of the grass yet stormed into the field with psychic wrath and the two waged war. Many now sane sheep men lay unconscious in the grass while others battled in utter rage with the goats. <br>
<br>
6. The War continued without either sides letting up head butts and sheep kicks filled the fields with bruises and bad headaches. The Goat leader known as &quot;The Goat&quot; called for reinforcements. <br>
<br>
7. More humans with hornes glued to their heads stormed the fields in waves of seventeens. The sheep held their ground battling as fierce as a man on all fours can battle. <br>
<br>
8. As the battle commenced five hours passed and now it seemed everyone was laying on the ground unconscious from head butts and sheep kicking. Slowly they began standing up again wobbling with a bad hang over. <br>
<br>
9. As they stood they noticed each other standing and their rage once again filled them. They gave battle again waging war for another seven hours until they became exhausted and tired. <br>
<br>
10. Sheep and Goat men alike began passing out in the grass from exhaustion and headaches but the war continued with three hour long breaks in between. <br>
<br>
11. Those that had become sane had no coordination on two legs and found themselves quickly overun by the goat during the battle and remained unconscious, never to wake again. <br>
<br>
12. The battles seemed to become shorter and shorter. Goat men and Sheep men began entering deep sleeps never to wage war again. <br>
<br>
13. The war waged on without either side letting up, the morning came and it seemed only sixteen combatants remained and one stranger that had not been fighting but walked upright with a pipe in his hand. <br>
<br>
14. The sixteen became ten two opposing sides and those waged war as the Man who held the pipe came closer his heart full of sorrow for the once great houses now reduced to ten fighting psychos. <br>
<br>
15. The two sets of five became two as the only two men remained. The Great Sheep King and The Goat who both stared at each other over the fallen bodies of their comrades. They met eyes and charged full speed at one another. <br>
<br>
16. The heads crashing was like a thunderous clap.. or maybe more like two heads hitting.. it was loud though. They both fell to the ground dizzy and unable to stand until they collapsed into a mess on the ground. <br>
<br>
17. The Man with the pipe was now very sad and looked over the bodies strewn out across the field and could do nothing for them. So he began playing his pipe. He was a Piper and his pipe was made of lead. <br>
<br>
18. He piped on his pipe the way pipers do with lead pipes until he could pipe no more. Upon finishing his song he decided to pipe some more for the dead even though he could no longer pipe he tried again and again. <br>
<br>
19. His lead piping did not go unnoticed the telepathic banana heard his melody that was for the fallen psychotics. While the Telepathic Banana rarely influenced world affairs instead having those do his deeds decided it was time. <br>
<br>
20. The telepathic banana dropped a banana from the sky that fell like.. a banana on to the head of the lead piper. Upon hitting him on the head the lead piper was blessed in a way that only the telepathic banana could bless people... with bananas. <br>
<br>
21. The Pipers pipe though lead turned yellow and his song spread through the fields and his countenance shined down on those around him. He piped and piped some more and the melody began healing all the fallen Goats and Sheep. <br>
<br>
22. Slowly one by one the goats and sheep woke from their sleep that no man should wake from less he have an awful headache.. and they did. The pipers melody slowly eased their headaches and pains. Confused and the weird man with a yellow pipe they decided not to continue fighting at this time. <br>
<br>
23. The Telepathic banana then sent a message to all those involved. That this Lead Piper would now be known as The Lead Piper Of Yellow as he was truly insane for feeling sad for The House of Goat, and The House of Sheep. Thus ended the first war of mammals.<br>
