The Path of Yellow Exposed <br>
<br>
<br>
The path of yellow though comical invites us to look at the fundamental truths inherit in all religions. The symbol used known, as &quot;The Telepathic Banana&quot; is a phallic symbol. It is a symbol of power and like a church steeple pointing towards heaven. The fruit itself is tropical and exotic eventually made popular in some macronations due to large plantation and free trade. The banana symbol is also yellow and yellow has been an archetype representing power like the blazing fire of god in other cultures. The fact that it is telepathic and can transcend language makes it increasingly god like in it's perspective. <br>
<br>
In the hero’s archetypal journey the hero always loses something that is never recovered and gains something instead. The story creates a full circle completing the hero’s journey. He begins as a normal wanderer as profession; he then looses his mind from dehydration and is then faced with an adversary that he confronts to find what he was lacking. Having this newfound knowledge he begins to spread the word. <br>
<br>
Once he creates the nation another full circle is spent as he is forced to abandon it with his partner forever leaving behind his past world but gaining a New World. This completes the hero's journey archetype but leaves another chapter to be written. <br>
<br>
The triangle is a repeating archetype having three sides of equal sides. Making it a powerful symbol for the subconscious mind. The triangle is used through out history to show places of worship a power. This power is sometimes represented as someone’s life’s work and a tribute to the gods such as the pyramids. <br>
<br>
The number three and the number five are both archetypes. The fact that these numbers are written shows that the original author was subject to the inner archetypes of man, a strong connection with universal unconscious mind. <br>
<br>
The image of the man on all fours represents the primal nature of human kind. The mans ability to speak both the language of a sheep and humans must imply the foundation of evolution. The sheep’s conversation from a four-legged archetypal follower into a member and leader in the path of yellow implies that some initiation process occurred. That the man went through steps accordingly to his status in the triangle. <br>
<br>
Since so many books are lost and have yet to be recovered and translated scholars must wait patiently for this dynamic faith to unfold to the public. Lets just hope their insanity has worn off enough for them to provide an accurate account of The Path of Yellows history.<br>
