The Endrathdelmarta <br>
<br>
<br>
1. The Man walked the beaches with no goal in life. He walked, and he would walk all day and all night with little rest, and no thought. He would look at his surroundings, and when he would turn away from them, he would forget what they where, and that he ever traveled them... <br>
<br>
2. Then, one day he stumbled upon a herd of sheep grazing in a somewhat hidden valley. This valley was glorious, filled with much grass, and many springs of sparkly blue water. He watched them for several hours, and was so captivated, that these hours turned to days, and then to several weeks. <br>
<br>
3. He noted the way they lived life, carefree, or seemingly so, and how they did as they wished, when they wished. He yearned to live like them, and attempted to do so with them. Doing so got him very wild, and crazed. After several days of extreme insanity, he had a dream. The leader of the herd, the mysterious talking sheep spoke to him, the sheep asked him questions about his life. What his goals where, and why he lived the way he did... The man had no true answer. He then, was inspired to think, and stewed for several days upon the question &quot;Why anything?&quot; <br>
<br>
4. He then decided he must go on a journey, a journey to find himself. On this sacred journey, he would bring along the Herd Leader, his new mentor/guide. He marched on with the sheep for several months and several wild hallucinations. All of them, pointing to one direction, and all of them involving the same mysterious yellow light. He traveled the sands of many small islands where he saw his past, present, and likely future. Only glimpses of each, where seen. After leaving the small islands, they found a larger island... <br>
<br>
5. This island was bathed in Soothing yellow light in one specific area, the wanderer’s destination. When he finally came upon the spot, he saw something he couldn’t believe, a lone banana amid a clearing. This banana seemed to be the cause of this light, and it spoke to him... &quot;Young man, you're journey to find yourself has brought you to me, and within me, you will find the path to yourself.&quot; The man walked over to the banana, and attempted to pick it up, he was unable to do so. And the banana vanished, along with the sheep. He then walked the beaches, confused, and angry for 5 days, when seemingly out of no where, he met a man, The Madman Of Yellow, then at that moment, he had a vision of a great temple, a magnificent city, and a powerful nation. <br>
<br>
Sidenote: Now from the location the man saw the banana, our 'Temple Of Radiance' resides.<br>
