Book of Yellow <br>
<br>
1. Then spoke the banana to the wanderers mind. &quot;I am the banana.&quot; and the wanderer felt the power of the mighty banana. The wanderer was puzzled by this dilema, even mad he was skeptical of this fruit. <br>
<br>
2. &quot;How can you speak to me?&quot; asked the mad wanderer. As he said these words a fisherman walked past with his daily catch. Sarcasticly answered for the banana, &quot;Maybe it's telepathic&quot;? The fisherman then laughed and walked on. <br>
<br>
3. So the banana became known as the telepathic one. The yellow banana seemed to look at the psychotic mad man through its sun yellow skin. &quot;I said I shall guide you.&quot; spoke the fruit in his hands. &quot;I shall show you the blazing glory of the might one in an hour yet to come.&quot; With those words the sun finally set and night fell upon them. <br>
<br>
